article.headline: Bradley 87, Creighton 59
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. (AP) -- Jeremy Crouch scored a game-high 20 points and four teammates scored in double digits as Bradley defeated Creighton 87-59 Saturday at Carver Arena. The Braves (15-12, 8-7 Missouri Valley) took the lead from the outset and never relinquished it. They went into halftime with a 46-26 advantage. The Bluejays (17-8, 8-7) shot just 34.4 percent (21-of-61) from the field for the game compared to 48.2 percent (27-of-56) for the Braves. Daniel Ruffin also scored 16 points for the Braves, Sam Maniscalco chipped in 15, Andrew Warren had 13 and Theron Wilson added 10. P'Allen Stinnett led the Bluejays in scoring with 18, Booker Woodfox had 16 and Dane Watts added 13.
